<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-09-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-09-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1074" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1074">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">Pulido</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Adee</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States of Venezuela</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-17"><hi rend="italic">September 17, 1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I share, with profound grief, the mourning
                            of the Government and people of the United States for the awful calamity
                            that has occurred at Galveston, and I present, as the interpreter of the
                            sentiments of my Government, the expression of its most sincere sympathy
                            to your excellency in this grievous juncture.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Augusto F.
                            Pulido.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>